[p]Good Morning Victorians.
[/p][p]We just released Hotfix 1.10.2, this is to mainly address the bug with fleets getting stuck and one other issue of Mustering Recruits as the Balkan League.
[/p][p]As a reminder, in 1.10.1 we introduced a temporary fix for Silesia being annexed by Prussia during a Polish Uprising, but are looking at a more robust solution for next week. 
[/p][p]Check out the full patchnotes below! Checksum is `750b`.
[/p][p]As always please report any bugs on [url="https://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/forums/victoria-3-bug-reports.1114/"][u]our bug reporting forums[/u][/url]! We have also updated the [url="https://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/threads/known-issues-update-1-10.1859597/"][u]Known Issues post for 1.10[/u][/url] with fixed issues!
[/p][p]The following changes have been made to the game compared to 1.10.1:[/p][h2]Bugfixes[/h2][list][*][p]Fixed fleet getting stuck in combat perpetually after war ending abruptly[/p][/*][*][p]Fixed fleet getting stuck in combat perpetually after ending an invasion manually[/p][/*][*][p]Fixed an issue where a movement disbanding would remove the "Movement Suppressed After Civil War" modifier, allowing it to reform and immediately revolt again[/p][/*][*][p]Fixed an issue where the "Muster Conscripts" button for the Balkan League could have its modifier excessively multiplied
[/p][/*][/list][p]*[b]Please note: If the fleet was already blocked before the hotfix it won’t be fixed by this hotfix, but it should prevent new fleets from getting stuck.[/b][/p][p][/p][p][b]Previous Patchnotes[/b][/p][p][url="https://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/developer-diary/victoria-3-dev-diary-160-national-awakening-update-1-10-now-live.1859612/"][u]1.10.0[/u][/url] | [url="https://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/threads/hotfix-1-10-1-is-now-live-not-for-problem-reports.1860263/"][u]1.10.1[/u][/url][/p]